gov.usgs.anss.metadata

Class SeedDumpToMetaData

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.metadata.SeedDumpToMetaData

  • public final class SeedDumpToMetaData
extends java.lang.Object
    This class processes a file dumped from rdseed -s into a SEEDStation and SEEDChannel representation and looks for problems. Normally, these structures are used to update the MetadataServer database (metadata tables station, channel, and response), the IRSAN databases at the ISC, and the IRServer database (irserver). The channels update are the "normalized metadata tables". The NormalizedToMeta process is used to convert these normalized tables into channelepoch, It can be run without database updates to allow parsing and inconsistency checks on other systems. The output can be voluminous with warnings marked by # marks and errors with asterisk (*).

    The processing done is quite complex analyzing the volume for inconsistencies and outputing and extensive list of variances from the NEIC expectations. 

       arg              Description
 -dbg            verbose output
 -elevatsurface  Run with elevation at surface (use if nometaupdate)
 -elevatdepth    Run with channel elevation at depth if buried (use if nometaupdate)
 -nometaupdate   Run this in parse mode and do not update the metadata server
 -noirserver     Run this in parse mode and do not update the IRServer database
 -iscdb   string Set the ISC database string rather than the default on
 -nometaupdate   Do not do the metadata update, only parse the flag and create the log files with variances
 -noirserver     Do not update the IRSAN/IADSR/etc at the ISC.  Updates of metadata database is still done.
 -localhost      Override all setting and use localhost for all operation (used in debugging)
 -addon           If set, all stations processed will be added onto the station rather than replacing them.  Used for serial metadata in different volumes
